body:
I have the following code:

```php
interface SettingCacheInterface
{
    /**
     * @psalm-param array<int, string> $array
     * @param string[] $array
     *
     * @psalm-return array<int, mixed>
     * @return mixed[]
     */
    public function fetchCache(array $array): array;
}

class MyClass 
{
    protected SettingCacheInterface $redis;

    /**
     * @psalm-param array<int, string> $keys
     *
     * @param string[] $keys
     * @param string   $code
     *
     * @psalm-return array<string, mixed>
     * @return array
     */
    protected function fetchFromCache(array $keys, string $code): array
    {
        $settings = $this->redis->fetchCache($keys);

        $data     = [];
        $keyCount = count($keys);
        for ($i = 0; $i < $keyCount; $i++) {
            if ($settings[$i] === false) {
                continue;
            }

            try {
                $value = unserialize($settings[$i]);
            } catch (Throwable $e) {
                $value = $settings[$i];
            }

            $data[$keys[$i]] = $value;
        }

        return $data;
    }
}
```

For `* @psalm-return array<string, mixed>` I got the following error: 
```
psalm: InvalidReturnType: The declared return type 'array<string, mixed>' for MyClass::fetchFromCache is incorrect, got 'array<string, mixed>'
```

For `return $data;` I got the following error:
```
psalm: InvalidReturnStatement: The inferred type 'array<string, mixed>' does not match the declared return type 'array<string, mixed>' for Neuffer\SharedBundle\APIRepository\SettingAPIRepository::fetchFromCache
```

I figured If I keep either the `try` part **OR** the `catch` part, no error is reported. I checked several times, in both case the `$value` ends up as `mixed` type. 

```bash
application@c936432a5411:/app$ vendor/bin/psalm -v
Psalm 3.18.2@19aa905f7c3c7350569999a93c40ae91ae4e1626
```

